# Blog Post Guidelines

## Content Structure

### Frontmatter Requirements
```yaml
---
title: "Descriptive Title"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
tags: [tag1, tag2]
description: "Brief description for SEO and social sharing"
---
```

### Post Organization
- Start with a compelling introduction
- Use clear section headings (H2, H3)
- Include relevant images with alt text
- End with a conclusion or call to action
- Keep paragraphs short and focused

## Writing Style

### Tone and Voice
- Write in a personal, conversational tone
- Be clear and direct
- Use active voice
- Avoid jargon unless necessary
- Include personal experiences when relevant

### Content Formatting
- Use proper markdown syntax
- Include code blocks with language specification
- Use blockquotes for important quotes
- Create lists for multiple points
- Use emphasis (bold/italic) sparingly

## Media and Examples

### Image Guidelines
- Optimize images before adding
- Use descriptive filenames
- Include alt text for accessibility
- Specify image dimensions
- Use relative paths for local images

### Code Examples
- Use syntax highlighting
- Keep examples focused and relevant
- Include comments for clarity
- Test code before including
- Link to full examples when available

## SEO and Accessibility

### Required Elements
- Descriptive title
- Meta description
- Relevant tags
- Proper heading structure
- Alt text for images

### Best Practices
- Use descriptive URLs
- Include internal links
- Add external references
- Use proper heading hierarchy
- Optimize for readability

## Post Types

### Technical Posts
- Start with problem statement
- Include relevant code examples
- Explain technical decisions
- Link to documentation
- Provide working solutions

### Personal Posts
- Share personal experiences
- Include relevant context
- Reflect on lessons learned
- Connect with readers
- Maintain authenticity

### Tutorial Posts
- Break down complex topics
- Include step-by-step instructions
- Provide working examples
- Anticipate common issues
- Include troubleshooting tips
